cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both the software and the accompanying paper."
title: "fluxcharge: symbolic Hamiltonians for lumped-element superconducting circuits"
abstract: >-
  A Python package that builds the flux-charge symmetric (LCG) Lagrangian of a
  lumped-element superconducting circuit (capacitors, inductors, Josephson
  junctions, quantum phase slips, gyrators) and reduces it to an analytical
  Hamiltonian following the constraint analysis of Salcedo, Cocquyt, Osborne and
  Houck.
type: software
version: 0.2.0
date-released: "2026-06-29"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/cgs2155/Flux-Charge-Symmetric-Circuits"
authors:
